line_1: As there he bides, it so befell,
line_2: The Wind came rustling down a Dell,

line_1: The dangers which her way had since befel,
line_2: Which clothed him in a form she loved so well:

line_1: I now will all declare that me befell
line_2: THE Squire of Dames his tale thus 'gan to tell;

line_1: After so many chances had befell,
line_2: It came into a mead of asphodel:

line_1: By thee, worse plagues than Pharaoh's land befel,
line_2: Diffus'd, make earth the vestibule of hell:

line_1: Sing heavenly muse; for what befel
line_2: Thou saw'st, and only thou can'st tell.
